{"id":349,"parent_id":325,"book_id":1,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":349,"title":"2 Kings 24","subtitle":"","short_title":"2 Kgs.","uri":"/scriptures/ot/2-kgs/24","content":[["div",[".titleNumber","Chapter 24"],[".studySummary",["i","Jerusalem is besieged and taken by Nebuchadnezzar—Many of the people of Judah are carried captive into Babylon—Zedekiah becomes king in Jerusalem—He rebels against Babylon."]]],[".bodyBlock",["div",{"id":"1","uri":"/scriptures/ot/2-kgs/24.1","order":"02.13.024.27390"},["b","1"],"In his days",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_1a"},"Nebuchadnezzar"],"king of Babylon came up, and Jehoiakim became his servant three years: then he turned and rebelled against him."],["div",{"id":"2","uri":"/scriptures/ot/2-kgs/24.2","order":"02.13.024.27391"},["b","2"],"And the",["span.smallCaps","Lord"],"sent",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_2a"},"against"],"him bands of the",["sup","b"],["a",{"href":"fn_2b"},"Chaldees"],", and bands of the Syrians, and bands of the Moabites, and bands of the children of Ammon, and sent them against Judah to",["sup","c"],["a",{"href":"fn_2c"},"destroy"],"it, according to the",["sup","d"],["a",{"href":"fn_2d"},"word"],"of the",["span.smallCaps","Lord"],", which he spake by his servants the prophets."],["div",{"id":"3","uri":"/scriptures/ot/2-kgs/24.3","order":"02.13.024.27392"},["b","3"],"Surely at the commandment of the",["span.smallCaps","Lord"],"came",["i","this"],"upon Judah, to remove",["i","them"],"out of his sight, for the",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_3a"},"sins"],"of",["sup","b"],["a",{"href":"fn_3b"},"Manasseh"],", according to all that he did;"],["div",{"id":"4","uri":"/scriptures/ot/2-kgs/24.4","order":"02.13.024.27393"},["b","4"],"And also for the innocent blood that he",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_4a"},"shed"],": for he filled Jerusalem with innocent blood; which the",["span.smallCaps","Lord"],"would not pardon."],["div",{"id":"5","uri":"/scriptures/ot/2-kgs/24.5","order":"02.13.024.27394"},["b","5"],"¶Now the rest of the acts of",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_5a"},"Jehoiakim"],", and all that he did,",["i","are"],"they not written in the book of the chronicles of the kings of Judah?"],["div",{"id":"6","uri":"/scriptures/ot/2-kgs/24.6","order":"02.13.024.27395"},["b","6"],"So",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_6a"},"Jehoiakim"],"slept with his fathers: and Jehoiachin his son reigned in his stead."],["div",{"id":"7","uri":"/scriptures/ot/2-kgs/24.7","order":"02.13.024.27396"},["b","7"],"And the king of Egypt came not again any more out of his land: for the king of Babylon had taken from the river of Egypt unto the river Euphrates all that pertained to the king of Egypt."],["div",{"id":"8","uri":"/scriptures/ot/2-kgs/24.8","order":"02.13.024.27397"},["b","8"],"¶Jehoiachin",["i","was"],["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_8a"},"eighteen"],"years old when he began to reign, and he reigned in Jerusalem three months. And his mother’s name",["i","was"],"Nehushta, the daughter of Elnathan of Jerusalem."],["div",{"id":"9","uri":"/scriptures/ot/2-kgs/24.9","order":"02.13.024.27398"},["b","9"],"And he did",["i","that which was"],"evil in the sight of the",["span.smallCaps","Lord"],", according to all that his father had done."],["div",{"id":"10","uri":"/scriptures/ot/2-kgs/24.10","order":"02.13.024.27399"},["b","10"],"¶At that time the servants of Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon came up against Jerusalem, and the city was",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_10a"},"besieged"],"."],["div",{"id":"11","uri":"/scriptures/ot/2-kgs/24.11","order":"02.13.024.27400"},["b","11"],"And",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_11a"},"Nebuchadnezzar"],"king of Babylon came against the city, and his servants did besiege it."],["div",{"id":"12","uri":"/scriptures/ot/2-kgs/24.12","order":"02.13.024.27401"},["b","12"],"And",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_12a"},"Jehoiachin"],"the king of Judah went out to the king of",["sup","b"],["a",{"href":"fn_12b"},"Babylon"],", he, and his mother, and his servants, and his princes, and his officers: and the king of Babylon took him in the eighth year of his reign."],["div",{"id":"13","uri":"/scriptures/ot/2-kgs/24.13","order":"02.13.024.27402"},["b","13"],"And he",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_13a"},"carried"],"out thence all the",["sup","b"],["a",{"href":"fn_13b"},"treasures"],"of the house of the",["span.smallCaps","Lord"],", and the treasures of the king’s house, and cut in pieces all the",["sup","c"],["a",{"href":"fn_13c"},"vessels"],"of gold which",["sup","d"],["a",{"href":"fn_13d"},"Solomon"],"king of Israel had made in the temple of the",["span.smallCaps","Lord"],", as the",["span.smallCaps","Lord"],"had said."],["div",{"id":"14","uri":"/scriptures/ot/2-kgs/24.14","order":"02.13.024.27403"},["b","14"],"And he",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_14a"},"carried away"],"all Jerusalem, and all the princes, and all the mighty men of valour,",["i","even"],"ten thousand captives, and all the craftsmen and",["sup","b"],["a",{"href":"fn_14b"},"smiths"],": none remained, save the poorest sort of the people of the land."],["div",{"id":"15","uri":"/scriptures/ot/2-kgs/24.15","order":"02.13.024.27404"},["b","15"],"And he carried away",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_15a"},"Jehoiachin"],"to Babylon, and the king’s mother, and the king’s wives, and his officers, and the",["sup","b"],["a",{"href":"fn_15b"},"mighty"],"of the land,",["i","those"],"carried he into",["sup","c"],["a",{"href":"fn_15c"},"captivity"],"from Jerusalem to",["sup","d"],["a",{"href":"fn_15d"},"Babylon"],"."],["div",{"id":"16","uri":"/scriptures/ot/2-kgs/24.16","order":"02.13.024.27405"},["b","16"],"And all the men of might,",["i","even"],"seven thousand, and craftsmen and smiths a thousand, all",["i","that were"],"strong",["i","and"],"apt for war, even them the king of Babylon brought captive to Babylon."],["div",{"id":"17","uri":"/scriptures/ot/2-kgs/24.17","order":"02.13.024.27406"},["b","17"],"¶And the king of Babylon made",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_17a"},"Mattaniah"],"his father’s brother king in his stead, and changed his name to",["sup","b"],["a",{"href":"fn_17b"},"Zedekiah"],"."],["div",{"id":"18","uri":"/scriptures/ot/2-kgs/24.18","order":"02.13.024.27407"},["b","18"],["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_18a"},"Zedekiah"],["i","was"],"twenty and one years old when he began to reign, and he reigned eleven years in Jerusalem. And his mother’s name",["i","was"],"Hamutal, the daughter of Jeremiah of Libnah."],["div",{"id":"19","uri":"/scriptures/ot/2-kgs/24.19","order":"02.13.024.27408"},["b","19"],"And he did",["i","that which was"],["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_19a"},"evil"],"in the sight of the",["span.smallCaps","Lord"],", according to all that Jehoiakim had done."],["div",{"id":"20","uri":"/scriptures/ot/2-kgs/24.20","order":"02.13.024.27409"},["b","20"],"For through the anger of the",["span.smallCaps","Lord"],"it came to pass in Jerusalem and Judah, until he had cast them out from his presence, that",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_20a"},"Zedekiah"],["sup","b"],["a",{"href":"fn_20b"},"rebelled"],"against the king of Babylon."]]],"refs":[["div",{"id":"1a","uri":"/scriptures/ot/2-kgs/24.1a","order":"02.13.024.27410"},["b","1a"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/2-chr/36.6.6-10"},"2 Chr. 36:6 (6–10)"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/dan/1.1.1-2"},"Dan. 1:1 (1–2)"],"."],["div",{"id":"2a","uri":"/scriptures/ot/2-kgs/24.2a","order":"02.13.024.27412"},["b","2a"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/ezek/19.8"},"Ezek. 19:8"],"."],["div",{"id":"2b","uri":"/scriptures/ot/2-kgs/24.2b","order":"02.13.024.27414"},["b","2b"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/job/1.17"},"Job 1:17"],"."],["div",{"id":"2c","uri":"/scriptures/ot/2-kgs/24.2c","order":"02.13.024.27416"},["b","2c"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/jer/25.9.9-11"},"Jer. 25:9 (9–11)"],"."],["div",{"id":"2d","uri":"/scriptures/ot/2-kgs/24.2d","order":"02.13.024.27418"},["b","2d"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/2-kgs/21.14.12-16"},"2 Kgs. 21:14 (12–16)"],";",["